Because the current code has some oddities, for example the `elif isinstance(threshold, numbers.Real): pass` followed by `elif not isinstance(threshold, numbers.Real)`.

There is no reason not to keep the same structure as before:

``` python
if isinstance(threshold, str):
    ...
elif isinstance(threshold, numbers.Real):
    # Note that includes int in contrary to your current code
else:
    raise TypeError(...)
```
